N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 208.16 - Discontinuance of actions

State Regulations

In any discontinued action, the attorney for
the plaintiff shall file a stipulation or statement of discontinuance with the
clerk of the court within 20 days of such discontinuance. If the action has
been noticed for judicial activity within 20 days of such discontinuance, the
stipulation or statement shall be filed before the date scheduled for such
activity. Notes
